parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel level sensor can cause the fuel gauge to malfunction, leading to inaccurate readings, which can result in running out of fuel, stalling, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Fuel gauge reads empty when the tank is full
fuel gauge fluctuates erratically
fuel gauge stays on empty
warning light and sound go off
and the vehicle may stall or run out of fuel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various malfunctions, including window and mirror malfunctions, engine stalling, and loss of power, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Driver-side window opens and closes independently
side mirror moves forward and backward independently
engine shuts off
and electrical system becomes inoperable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various malfunctions, including loss of headlights, brake lights, and other essential systems, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Headlights turn off while driving
passenger side headlight and rear lights keep burning out
lights start dimming while driving
windshield wipers fail to turn on and off
airbag deactivation light comes on and off
heater blower motor relay gets hot and melts the connector
and fuel gauge shows empty when the tank is full.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the engine to shut off while driving, leading to loss of power steering and brakes, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Engine shuts off while driving
key will not turn after shutting off the engine
and ignition switch failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Stabilitrak system can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Stabilitrak light comes on and off
traction control off button does not work
and strange noise when the Stabilitrak system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and transmission can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
and engine shuts off while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to loss of power and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Fuel gauge shows empty when the tank is full
fuel level sensor light comes on and off
and fuel pump failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the BCM can cause various malfunctions, including loss of headlights, brake lights, and other essential systems, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Headlights turn off while driving
passenger side headlight and rear lights keep burning out
and lights start dimming while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the HDM can cause the headlights to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, especially at night.
symptoms: Headlights flicker or turn off while driving
low beam headlights do not work
daytime running lights do not work
headlights turn off and then come back on
intermittent headlight failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Wiring issues can cause electrical malfunctions, including headlight failure, which can lead to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Wiring melts
headlight failure
intermittent headlight failure
low beam headlights do not work.
